# Build output
build/
*.o
*.s
*.d

# Editor / OS
.cache/
compile_commands.json
*.swp
.DS_Store

# Python bits used by the upstream test mirrors
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/

# Files generated by the instrumented tests
tsan.supp
tests/syzygy
tests/bench_tmp.epd

# The NNUE net. A RUNTIME INPUT, not a build product: `./build.sh net` reports
# where it must be and never downloads, so a clean build never touches the
# network. It is ~106 MiB and changes with upstream, which is reason enough --
# but the deciding one is that committing it would make the bench anchor look
# like a property of this repository rather than of a file fetched separately.
**/*.nnue

# Throwaway checkouts made for isolated agent runs; never part of the tree.
.claude/worktrees/

# Profiler and memcheck output from the local-only tools in tools/ (see
# docs/09-tooling-ci.md). `perf_callgrind.sh` writes `callgrind.out` into the
# CURRENT directory unless OUT= names one, and that file is routinely larger
# than the whole repository -- it is measurement, never a result to keep.
callgrind.out*
cachegrind.out*
callgrind.annotate*
massif.out*
vgcore.*
perf.data*
*.profraw
*.profdata

# A binary built outside build/. `BIN=` is honoured by every build.sh step
# (build.sh:10) and `arch-determinism` uses it per ISA tier, so an engine can
# land wherever the caller points it; guard the plain names at the repo root.
/mcfish
/mcfish-*

# External runtime inputs: the NNUE net, the Syzygy tables fetched by
# `./build.sh tb-fetch`, and an opening book if one is ever added. Things the
# engine CONSUMES, never repository artefacts -- the 3-man Syzygy set alone is
# 10 binary files, and the `tb` gate reports plainly when they are absent rather
# than passing quietly. `./build.sh` runs the engine from here (RESOURCES_DIR).
resources/
*.rtbw
*.rtbz

# Dev-only scratch: milestone plans, port-progress tracking, reports. The port is
# finished; these are history, not authoritative docs. Never in the repo surface.
__DEV/
